trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection"></xref> class contains a collection of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> objects.

The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection.Contains(System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference)"></xref> method determines if the collection contains specified <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> object to locate.
`true` if the collection contains value or `false` if it does not.

The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection.CopyTo(System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference[],System.Int32)"></xref> method copies the entire collection to a one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.
A one-dimensional array that is the destination of the elements copied from the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection"></xref> object.
The zero-based index of values where copying begins.
values is a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic).
index is less than zero.
values is multidimensional
-or-
The number of elements in the source is greater than the available space from index to the end of the destination values.
The type of the source cannot be cast automatically to the type of the destination array.

The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection.IndexOf(System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference)"></xref> method returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence of the specified <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> object in <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> object for which the index is returned.
The index value of the specified <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> object, if found.
If the object is not found, this method returns -1.
The property contains the object at the specified index.
The index value of the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> object.
The object at the specified index.
